{
  "nova|tts-1|It is a truth universally acknowledged, that a single man in possession of a good fortune must be in want of a wife.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/5fc441e812420b1eee3168e9d47c2ac4d82df10b.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|However little known the feelings or views of such a man may be on his first entering a neighbourhood, this truth is so well fixed in the minds of the surrounding families, that he is considered as the rightful property of some one or other of their daughters.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/803ec0dcf791010c26a82deb3df20000560c0bb6.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“My dear Mr. Bennet,” said his lady to him one day, “have you heard that Netherfield Park is let at last?”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/a3013ff45833cbe327f233bc9029dcb05598330a.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Mr. Bennet replied that he had not.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/5a7986b115ff54a7adc893afb16d8eff44f452ea.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“But it is,” returned she; “for Mrs. Long has just been here, and she told me all about it.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b83920a2be1087012021b50f4ca13ad58a84221b.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Mr. Bennet made no answer.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/bfb7b48e203ff2c16ffedca3d0f129e4853aea38.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Do not you want to know who has taken it?” cried his wife, impatiently.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/996deec9bf85c54d730e40ac39e03a4b192921e4.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“_You_ want to tell me, and I have no objection to hearing it.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/91111b6fc0e2ae04fce061246b818118405807ae.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|[Illustration:": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/753012f44fed2f45496939397bbc14adf59be0d4.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“He came down to see the place”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/191aaf2c3dd67e3e23e5e40078bdffe669f38945.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|[_Copyright 1894 by George Allen._]]": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/0c3bae2e3cecf7324f74e126ea9a9f0e29b04b6e.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|This was invitation enough.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/fd84947e6eb4524334c266665e9f8969f4d92c77.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Why, my dear, you must know, Mrs. Long says that Netherfield is taken by a young man of large fortune from the north of England; that he came down on Monday in a chaise and four to see the place, and was so much delighted with it that he agreed with Mr. Morris immediately; that he is to take possession before Michaelmas, and some of his servants are to be in the house by the end of next week.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b4e112efd491e2d5e51a5b56b324c65e53cc8747.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“What is his name?”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/c32ee0ad962e75e9648da5048ca477351576560f.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Bingley.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/646fed193e7aeef1ec4b56d8a96b1da18c3fc647.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Is he married or single?”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/0ac0cb370d9d2b175a2cf0729e140e26c0b2083e.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Oh, single, my dear, to be sure!": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/6667508540c9d8361c00016a461bb51b7f16c405.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|A single man of large fortune; four or five thousand a year.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/61bb0f968b9a78d1c34f7b866de02cbca99663ba.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|What a fine thing for our girls!”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/16a8e0b0f5a1c866152b551e41258c76c8945885.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“How so?": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b21e7e5e2fdc54308788cc183864e6a667b923da.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|how can it affect them?”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/25c8d251c73bfb2f332c38e5aae5c307b0499e93.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“My dear Mr. Bennet,” replied his wife, “how can you be so tiresome?": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/3be41014665b273c2f651fe1b2d64637d5ccf891.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|You must know that I am thinking of his marrying one of them.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/1817565520c6f9ca00e49e6c639e61cc111b9183.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Is that his design in settling here?”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/5a1f63a93509ffac440ce663c38abe0f1ca20e96.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Design?": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/2dde06f79a06ef54ad1d508751bf5f902275a208.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Nonsense, how can you talk so!": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/0981aa8aeb7f10a101b214ef46c05e51f04c8ece.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|But it is very likely that he _may_ fall in love with one of them, and therefore you must visit him as soon as he comes.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/53ff36d8e8b45abd6619aaa5bd6b910b33378260.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I see no occasion for that.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/0476153f75a8cad63f5f24d4a454d85b106e1b78.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|You and the girls may go--or you may send them by themselves, which perhaps will be still better; for as you are as handsome as any of them, Mr. Bingley might like you the best of the party.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/01eeb735bf2ec43d33c005b8cb1236bbf15e0e95.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“My dear, you flatter me.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/37b824f3f34bbe3c4ce6e0f3205e8dad8e07a6c9.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|I certainly _have_ had my share of beauty, but I do not pretend to be anything extraordinary now.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/6f96c61d0e34f62677e39e93995ff84c68c98ca1.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|When a woman has five grown-up daughters, she ought to give over thinking of her own beauty.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/ad32d0633544a95c66f338a94bb5976895619929.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“In such cases, a woman has not often much beauty to think of.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/49362c155074d21bd1e4d84f01da7ff627f13565.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“But, my dear, you must indeed go and see Mr. Bingley when he comes into the neighbourhood.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/75eadf4b2ecd3e9eb72b5e92b7a712c0b53a9931.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“It is more than I engage for, I assure you.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/29c0f083f31bec2acc2d9e6b3cf6305cea6c0aa6.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“But consider your daughters.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/8c2e492e3c9088121024ea914904dc7b666ddd72.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Only think what an establishment it would be for one of them.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/f54304371abce1b9993e12a5448272097534b40d.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Sir William and Lady Lucas are determined to go, merely on that account; for in general, you know, they visit no new comers.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/595da41c050da2d4db4a8e4c867efcc362082f45.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Indeed you must go, for it will be impossible for _us_ to visit him, if you do not.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b57f74b8841c14887b8c1a2e5d12eb0af155cc0b.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“You are over scrupulous, surely.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/9676cadb013bf93ab45ad37d54d680744615d69d.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|I dare say Mr. Bingley will be very glad to see you; and I will send a few lines by you to assure him of my hearty consent to his marrying whichever he chooses of the girls--though I must throw in a good word for my little Lizzy.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/6ab4bdc9ce6c522fd1a2bb8564a70cb0234f1a72.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I desire you will do no such thing.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/42cee8173e37ec8d5fc2de137bc0cbc08ab5d71e.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Lizzy is not a bit better than the others: and I am sure she is not half so handsome as Jane, nor half so good-humoured as Lydia.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/5f51ca9036ef6fb7d7a296402b901f7e1c0495b7.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|But you are always giving _her_ the preference.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/90f769edd4b1c05828339688e9e2ad9a7e8f54dd.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“They have none of them much to recommend them,” replied he: “they are all silly and ignorant like other girls; but Lizzy has something more of quickness than her sisters.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/6f59bf209f8da6e3e3664c0f088ed366224ff5e6.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Mr.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/510ed9adb484c19eba6296c581bf0a28e97276e7.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Bennet, how can you abuse your own children in such a way?": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/47b282cfe42f3b03f4647fe5f02cb9b62c63aea0.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|You take delight in vexing me.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/37947bcce989b29d6fc8d214ce55daa55c95c047.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|You have no compassion on my poor nerves.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/98e681f8e56178b9a52cb120805c8f4495e0f749.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“You mistake me, my dear.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/1f61692703dfcbb459ae6fbcd65db61f42542da9.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|I have a high respect for your nerves.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/543ba4309683fe6c7dec64e10eac8d6305bf2468.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|They are my old friends.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/f6b263cf48f39e32f2a57597362f940dcc3d81d1.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|I have heard you mention them with consideration these twenty years at least.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/388a982da5aac04a9ddddefcf8b589cddb2a0400.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Ah, you do not know what I suffer.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/9fbebda559fb059c85f2ad46424c12d37979492f.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“But I hope you will get over it, and live to see many young men of four thousand a year come into the neighbourhood.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/c18c589c895011a5d56ee439525f5113587427ef.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“It will be no use to us, if twenty such should come, since you will not visit them.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/a64e5e416d6d0766ccdb0babf94153434a1ac4d9.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Depend upon it, my dear, that when there are twenty, I will visit them all.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/c3e7799fe0350e702663893724d7a870620ec402.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Mr. Bennet was so odd a mixture of quick parts, sarcastic humour, reserve, and caprice, that the experience of three-and-twenty years had been insufficient to make his wife understand his character.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/624dad19d676e6bfe1dbd556581c61a5611f5307.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|_Her_ mind was less difficult to develope.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/746fcbb79b0fd6420b5868b2e5d74dd42698d115.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|She was a woman of mean understanding, little information, and uncertain temper.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/500b28ef0244d7b891b6e48071d3159e65825069.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|When she was discontented, she fancied herself nervous.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/fccb72b3d1dee36702b07f8c1b303a02da6715ea.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|The business of her life was to get her daughters married: its solace was visiting and news.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b7536e0ab6edb15861bd382038f665680c54c45b.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|[Illustration: M^{r.} & M^{rs.} Bennet": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/35b103c2546123d5766f5665c2d4e583cd70b01b.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I hope Mr. Bingley will like it”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/eb1d6f3565a2c93e9d7d1c5cf1117bbe09dab845.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|[Illustration]": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/5728f673570833934285f49a1b4514771cd27bff.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Mr. Bennet was among the earliest of those who waited on Mr. Bingley.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/acb3bb6cdaf952c8484de2d984813860f5a0cb2a.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|He had always intended to visit him, though to the last always assuring his wife that he should not go; and till the evening after the visit was paid she had no knowledge of it.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/27a427de5f70ef00e03770a571e083cb1dfd7948.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|It was then disclosed in the following manner.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/fbf012527c52ac91f9533b44e9498d5a8852ac8e.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Observing his second daughter employed in trimming a hat, he suddenly addressed her with,--": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/5a65f4e6bdabc80d896d9d983d8138e7d88e412d.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I hope Mr. Bingley will like it, Lizzy.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/da055cdc2d741a7c8d8a4bef5bb74af698f3cbee.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“We are not in a way to know _what_ Mr. Bingley likes,” said her mother, resentfully, “since we are not to visit.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/4e0b19bbf3a02ddcc05cb3a72ace9f17a217199e.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“But you forget, mamma,” said Elizabeth, “that we shall meet him at the assemblies, and that Mrs. Long has promised to introduce him.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/a1e9e4cc426a2252e6bc254ae6e90508af0ba453.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I do not believe Mrs. Long will do any such thing.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/17c92c09f9c7f1f03297b524f93ea094a79050dd.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|She has two nieces of her own.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/24278629c5d9be8c459b1b06f7f05322fcdb5f0c.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|She is a selfish, hypocritical woman, and I have no opinion of her.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/33633130bafeee0f35258c86f07cb6fa693579e8.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“No more have I,” said Mr. Bennet; “and I am glad to find that you do not depend on her serving you.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b0a71122b805eac5668d7f28f0d0cecd9e07a14c.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Mrs. Bennet deigned not to make any reply; but, unable to contain herself, began scolding one of her daughters.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/81f28be421e7e83990820dfae4574219bd994edf.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Don’t keep coughing so, Kitty, for heaven’s sake!": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/23ea277bec6b2bf8de467ae31f06666d90ad033d.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Have a little compassion on my nerves.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/cd2eb133fdc5f71efd365428187a1c0e27d56ac0.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|You tear them to pieces.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/bf358fc12c8a37bd5febf35aa6d9b2a4145cc22b.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Kitty has no discretion in her coughs,” said her father; “she times them ill.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/0833f7bf579ea7b0ba480a4a0265471309a55025.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I do not cough for my own amusement,” replied Kitty, fretfully.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/8b8429d7c85d685c54f0dad765ec510446033d09.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“When is your next ball to be, Lizzy?”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/e5a2e63429c594bc0054125bb8849e97138d7f10.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“To-morrow fortnight.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/504ad4049dfb3101fe94d57b164cc40de7a7eea3.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Ay, so it is,” cried her mother, “and Mrs. Long does not come back till the day before; so, it will be impossible for her to introduce him, for she will not know him herself.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/a06e9b2539cd95145f88d0e11ec53ea5c1124960.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Then, my dear, you may have the advantage of your friend, and introduce Mr. Bingley to _her_.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/6270d62cc44a40eb5a931ffda1b07e56d15ae2b6.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Impossible, Mr. Bennet, impossible, when I am not acquainted with him myself; how can you be so teasing?”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/988e8f21a301cc4b9e8222a0504a9938d7c069a2.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I honour your circumspection.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/99d024f1c10caeb444a232654035dd02f1ca8357.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|A fortnight’s acquaintance is certainly very little.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/04de6c6b3746d8bfa345bc49cfaff359278d2511.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|One cannot know what a man really is by the end of a fortnight.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/2e1fa68e89089536c12b4cdb5d91e68a43214806.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|But if _we_ do not venture, somebody else will; and after all, Mrs. Long and her nieces must stand their chance; and, therefore, as she will think it an act of kindness, if you decline the office, I will take it on myself.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/44a5a751d0a265f79c3bac9f122fe01bbe6f8284.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|The girls stared at their father.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/478d23ccc34cfa1e0aaa96ea8153c32bfca6e976.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Mrs. Bennet said only, “Nonsense, nonsense!”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/54bfeac1bf5c4e75b831bd03294ad3309177e8bd.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“What can be the meaning of that emphatic exclamation?” cried he.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b270c63dfba39cc1d41da308ce0d11567c256fd3.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Do you consider the forms of introduction, and the stress that is laid on them, as nonsense?": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/fc0a718a98ec38d4e0e9a5b184de802da8bcbc72.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|I cannot quite agree with you _there_.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/68b73be664adc1c4853c8c7ac3e53ef080a9c330.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|What say you, Mary?": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/5ce47f26e9189c6908aa958f79352b6b2d8ba306.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|For you are a young lady of deep reflection, I know, and read great books, and make extracts.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/67a5f013bf5f60e1c87544cbffac2e335d1707c7.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Mary wished to say something very sensible, but knew not how.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/12f726b4f004bdd44b415fbef6e2d7cad5353635.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“While Mary is adjusting her ideas,” he continued, “let us return to Mr. Bingley.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b96cf60d651a4fcc17b93fec71f9b80e8de7e2cb.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I am sick of Mr. Bingley,” cried his wife.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/2ae52b76ec20e013ecef9ddc061822af43459234.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I am sorry to hear _that_; but why did you not tell me so before?": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/4bdc6d4a7984c57aa59fccb469ef7f2dfbc3c889.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|If I had known as much this morning, I certainly would not have called on him.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/14b8b6c7e0cbf8c7538ea2579eb97ba7cdc481a6.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|It is very unlucky; but as I have actually paid the visit, we cannot escape the acquaintance now.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/f58091f61ffc0a9d1ae2a50dcb0d3c1fdd278470.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|The astonishment of the ladies was just what he wished--that of Mrs. Bennet perhaps surpassing the rest; though when the first tumult of joy was over, she began to declare that it was what she had expected all the while.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/4e9d17b89ba0519febe4fe1c9bc39d887b8dd088.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“How good it was in you, my dear Mr. Bennet!": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/96c904e950ac97b9e0764816bc13a672e3957f41.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|But I knew I should persuade you at last.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/8b932082427c60ab953febcb57b352b805d89bf8.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|I was sure you loved your girls too well to neglect such an acquaintance.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/2963f9780b7090028a02c6a17d5585f82fb4b104.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Well, how pleased I am!": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/14f20c5f201d8ebd9e099eba62de0dceda6c3432.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|And it is such a good joke, too, that you should have gone this morning, and never said a word about it till now.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/fcadcd7f2fdf40870c304ed725a56929d21d482c.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Now, Kitty, you may cough as much as you choose,” said Mr. Bennet; and, as he spoke, he left the room, fatigued with the raptures of his wife.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/c9e8bf104a2a70611ca40b747924a5966bde2f61.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“What an excellent father you have, girls,” said she, when the door was shut.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/6d760bd000c07552e762a02f89d6d0bdd0b3321c.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“I do not know how you will ever make him amends for his kindness; or me either, for that matter.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/08acda4d5155c8c7475d0fbff3422c13d4c7406b.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|At our time of life, it is not so pleasant, I can tell you, to be making new acquaintances every day; but for your sakes we would do anything.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/b7bc7d23a86b73a67fd2d76cf8c42b378b669a12.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|Lydia, my love, though you _are_ the youngest, I dare say Mr. Bingley will dance with you at the next ball.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/584654b36ad0479384bca07b0349b9a0abe83045.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|“Oh,” said Lydia, stoutly, “I am not afraid; for though I _am_ the youngest, I’m the tallest.”": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/646277542c3b9dbd33e4edf0b7cc35b1aae9f60c.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|The rest of the evening was spent in conjecturing how soon he would return Mr. Bennet’s visit, and determining when they should ask him to dinner.": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/496739a386cb09e7cbdf62bdbaec6890db4eb826.mp3",
  "nova|tts-1|[Illustration: “I’m the tallest”]": "/audio/pride-and-prejudice/dc3e5f8fa62302ae76cdc9cc7280121afc99d090.mp3",
